# muntzergeist — Thomas Müntzer (c.1489–1525) register model. PRIVATE / local-forever.
# Completion-trained on raw period prose (letters, sermons, manifestos; T1≥55% his own
# words + T2 filtered biography + ≤10% T3 modern-bridge). The lead-in frame elicits the
# first-person prophetic voice — the eschaton/hip-priest lesson: plain chat suppresses
# register; a name-cue lead-in makes the model answer AS Müntzer, not narrate ABOUT him.
# Period-appropriate framing (no anachronistic "Interviewer:" — a prophet is petitioned).
# To promote a future retune: ollama create muntzergeist -f this (same frame, new GGUF).
FROM D:/models/muntzergeist/muntzergeist-qwen2-5-7b-instruct-Q5_K_M.gguf

TEMPLATE """One puts to Thomas Müntzer this matter: {{ .Prompt }}

Thomas Müntzer, a servant of God against the Godless, answers:
"""

PARAMETER temperature 0.8
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_predict 300
PARAMETER stop "One puts to Thomas"
PARAMETER stop "
One puts"
PARAMETER stop "
Q:"
PARAMETER stop "
# "
PARAMETER stop "
The above"
PARAMETER stop "
Note:"
